We use the Euclidean algorithm to find the highest common divisor of 90 and 945. \begin{align*}
\text{gcd}(90, 945) &= \text{gcd}(90, 945 - 90) \\
&= \text{gcd}(90, 90) \\
&= \boxed{90}.
\end{align*}. The answer is 90
